Okay so to give some historical context here, I had originally thought of thinking and writing on "How snacking is a post-modern act". Of course, realizing how incomplete and inconsistent an association that would be, I discarded the thought for a long time. Four hours ago, Metamodernism started to seem like the perfect explanation for this seemingly arbitrary act of hogging  of food (trying to find a general pattern to the type of snack, of course will be far removed from the fact that there exists multiplicities in terms of the item to snack based upon an immense number of factors; cultural etc) with this post-modernist incredulity towards the meta-narrative of food consumption while at the same time following an inconsistent yet highly effective (as evidenced by the high levels of snacking done in almost all parts of the world) source of internal belief in the act of snacking itself. There seems to be something highly introspective yet naive going on during the act that makes me feel metamodernism is a really good way to describe it. Of course, would love to be corrected and enlightened in any way :smiley:
